\section{Comprehensions}

\begin{note}
Any list or dictionary that contains the keyword \lstinline{for} inside of it is a \emph{comprehension}.
It is very easy to get \lstinline{IndexError}s or \lstinline{TypeError}s inside a list comprehension,
and the error messages can be hard to debug.
(Expect me to try to trick you on the quiz this way...)
\end{note}
